Can't really explain this but stage trace is too coincidental to be unaffected in some way by the visit - possibly plane parked directly on top of sensor or something along those lines. Assuming that DWL is valid as disregarding the DWL and applying a drift all the way from July 2020 to May 2022 results in almost the same correction at the moment of the visit on 2021-09-09 @14:40, only 0.002m different. Assuming that the sensor was affected during the visit and then returned to normal. Applying offset to bring stage trace back in line with before and after visit and modifying drifts on either side.
